## 8. Content Preservation Rules

Preserve the meaning of all project statuses.

The following points must remain accurate:

- LinkVerse is currently focused on bookmark features.
- LinkVerse currently includes bookmark, tag, and memo functionality.
- LinkVerse may become a platform for the user’s services in the long term.
- /orbit and /blog will be operated first.
- NexLetter uses GitHub and Slack data.
- NexLetter passes data through AI Agent pipelines.
- NexLetter generates weekly reports and sends them by email.
- NexLetter is currently waiting for Slack App review.
- NexLetter’s major challenges include unstructured Slack data, lack of test sources, token volume, rate limits, Railway worker operation, billing policy, and billing flow testing.
- The rate limit issue may include 429 Rate limit reached for gpt-4.1-mini.
- MarketReport is a service for publishing reports based on microeconomic, macroeconomic, and market-related sources.
- MarketReport uses n8n-based automation pipelines.
- The first stage of the report pipelines is nearly complete.
- Three report pipelines are currently close to completion.
- The next focus is how to present the registered data on web pages.
- Future directions include improving pipelines, increasing report types, using vector data for similarity measurement, and generating higher-level reports from similar reports.
- The current visible challenge is that the report text is strong, but there is not yet enough material or system structure for graphs, images, or visual support.

Do not overstate the maturity of any project.

For example:

Do not say:
- The platform is complete.
- The service is ready for launch.
- The pipeline is fully finished.
- The system already solves all data issues.

Use careful wording such as:
- nearly complete
- currently being considered
- still needs more testing
- remains a challenge
- may become important later
- the next issue to work through

